2022 Travel Wrap Up:
I did an impossible amount of traveling this year. Racked up miles, broke two suitcases, slept in the freezing desert, and currently have five world wonders under my belt. 
Slide 1: Pyramids of Giza, Egypt 
Slide 2: Chichén Itzá, Mexico
Slide 3: Petra, Jordan 
Slide 4: Karnak, Luxor, Egypt 
Slide 5: The Dead Sea, Jordan 
Slide 6: Grand Cayman 

Honorable mentions: Sosua, Dominican Republic. Wadi Rum, Jordan. Turks and Caicos. Jackson, Mississippi (That Honeybun Cake, Lawdddddd). 

No firm 2023 plans yet but I’m mad jealous of everyone in Ghana right now. Someone invite me to your auntie’s house! 

#nomadnesstribe #wanderlust #travelgram #egypt #jordan #tulum #
2022, I thank you. ❤️

Updates from the office of Tiffany D. Jackson:

-I will no longer accept school visit invitations unless there is a cancellation fee, in case “concerned” parents want to interfere. Please respect my time and the group effort it takes to make these visits special for kids! (This does not effect regular donated and prison visits)

-I am no longer giving media interviews about being banned. (Especially for free!) It’s upsetting and a distraction from the REAL work, which is to continue writing diverse thriller/horror books for kids and support educators in this ridiculous political battlefield. 

-Closed to blurbs until Nov. 2023.

Folks are going through battles you have no idea about. Remember to be kind or fuck around and find out. The power is yours!

Hey, so some of you are under the impression, per my photos, that all I do is travel…😂😂😂

What you don’t see is all the writing I do between these snap shots. I write on beaches, planes, ferries, trains, in dollar vans, and too many airport lounges to count. A good portion of MONDAY’S NOT COMING was written on a 15 hour flights to Abu Dhabi, then finished in South Africa. I wrote 18k words of GROWN on my phone while touring. I’ve edited chapters before West Indian carnivals and fetes. What was I doing before my best friends wedding (plural weddings)? Working on my deadlines. What did I do after funerals? Made sure I hit my word count. For every day in the sun, I’ve sat up until 2am struggling with copyedits. But my favorite time to write is 6am when the world is still sleep. My family is sick of seeing my laptop stapled to me like a 3rd arm. Also: Seasonal depression is real and I’m a true blue cancer. My need for beach and ocean waters during the months of Feb/March is critical for my survival. 

I have a BIG life outside of publishing with friends and family, and an insatiable craving for adventure. I don’t have kids or a desk I have to be stapled to. So I take full advantage of this privilege to be a mobile mogul. I’m grateful for this blessing, save my pennies, and don’t waste a precious minute. 

All that to say is YES, I’m working on new stuff but SHEESH! Y’all so bossy, yelling at me to get back to work. Can I live?? 😂😂😂

If you’re interested in following more black folks who travel, please check out @nomadnesstribe @blackgirlstraveltoo #nomadness

A beloved travel bae, my TV production sis, a Howard Bison, and a fierce Endo warrior. A bright light everywhere she went, well loved by a gang of women. 

It all happened so incredibly fast, too fast for any of us to wrap our heads around. I’m confused, heartbroken, lost for words. But I’m a believer and take comfort in knowing she’s no longer in pain. SHE has arrived with all her accoutrements and her hair laid!!

Rest well, girl. You deserve it more than anyone I know. ♥️
